<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Welcome on Gert's blog</title><link>https://gertalot.com/</link><description>Recent content in Welcome on Gert's blog</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-us</language><lastBuildDate>Sun, 26 Oct 2025 04:23:12 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://gertalot.com/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Development workflow with Claude superpowers</title><link>https://gertalot.com/posts/development-workflow-with-claude-superpowers/</link><pubDate>Sun, 26 Oct 2025 04:23:12 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://gertalot.com/posts/development-workflow-with-claude-superpowers/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;I have hardly written any code manually in the last year, yet I&amp;rsquo;ve built heaps of smaller and larger projects, using AI
to learn new things, write boilerplate code, resolve tricky bugs, and rapidly iterate on ideas.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I have journeyed from &lt;em&gt;AI autocomplete&lt;/em&gt; to &lt;em&gt;vibe coding&lt;/em&gt; to &lt;em&gt;prompt engineering&lt;/em&gt; to increasingly effective agentic
&lt;em&gt;spec-driven&lt;/em&gt; development workflows. For a while, I&amp;rsquo;ve been using and developing my trusty old prompts
from &lt;a href="https://github.com/gertalot/cursor-rules" target="_blank"&gt;my cursor-rules repo&lt;/a&gt; to help me keep the AI on track.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Claude YOLO: Not so dangerously skip permissions</title><link>https://gertalot.com/posts/claude-yolo-not-so-dangerously-skip-permissions/</link><pubDate>Sun, 26 Oct 2025 03:45:17 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://gertalot.com/posts/claude-yolo-not-so-dangerously-skip-permissions/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;I do all my development with &lt;a href="https://claude.com/claude-code" target="_blank"&gt;Claude Code&lt;/a&gt; and the spec-driven workflow &lt;em&gt;du jour&lt;/em&gt;.
Claude is usually great at letting me quickly explore new things and rapidly iterate on ideas.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you&amp;rsquo;ve used Claude Code, you will be as tired as I am to have to give Claude permission to do basically anything. Can
I edit this file? Yes, and don&amp;rsquo;t ask me again for similar commands. Can I run this script? Yes, and don&amp;rsquo;t ask me again
for similar commands, etcetera.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>About</title><link>https://gertalot.com/about/</link><pubDate>Thu, 23 Oct 2025 10:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://gertalot.com/about/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="about-me"&gt;About Me&lt;/h2&gt;
